The students are said to have used cigarette filters to light the fire which burnt the dormitory.Authorities warn students engaging in unlawful activities that will not be spared. Nine secondary school girls accused of setting a dormitory ablaze have been arrested by police in Kirinyaga County. 

The students from Mugumo Girls High School were seized Friday morning and locked up at Kianyaga Police Station for interrogation. 

They were said to have burnt a dormitory on Sunday last week, destroying property worth thousands of shillings. 



