Burnt dormitory 

During the arson incident, beds, mattresses and others items were reduced to ashes. 

However, county fire fighters and the police responded fast and managed to put out the fire which had thrown the learning institution management into panic. 

According to Gichugu East Sub-county Directorate of Criminal Investigations (DCI) officer, Millicent Ochuka, the students used cigarette filters to light the fire which burnt the dormitory. 

Arson charges 






"We have been carrying out investigations since the incident was reported but finally we have arrested the suspects," she said. 

Ms Ochuka said that the girls will soon be charged with arson adding that their parents were free to visit them at the police station. 

